  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 13259,
        "reputation" : 73352,
        "user_id" : 26510,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 99,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/25ee9a1b9f5a16feb1432882a9ef2f06?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Brad Parks",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/26510/brad-parks"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 3,
      "creation_date" : 1431695896,
      "post_id" : 25441276,
      "comment_id" : 48620819,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "thanks! this is the easiest way to just copy the libs that would be required by a project into a folder somewhere so you can copy them somewhere else if need be, e.g. a non maven based project. Note that of course you can just pass in a hardcoded folder to use if you like, e.g. <code>mvn dependency:copy-dependencies -DoutputDirectory=.&#47;lib </code>"
